library(ggplot2)

Part 1: 1.

#Generates a random sample of size 100,000 from uniform distribution
U <- runif(100000)

#Plots a histogram of the whole sample
ggplot() + geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.05, aes(U), fill = "black", color = "white")

2.

#Creates a data frame with 30 rows and 1001 columns, the first being the numbers 1 through 30, and the rest being the 1000 samples of size 30
Dist <- data.frame(c(1:30))
for(i in 1:1000){
  Dist <- cbind(Dist,sample(U, 30))
}
colnames(Dist) <- c("n", seq(1:1000))

3 and 4.

#Saves the mean of each sample (each column except the first) as Avgs
Avgs <- colMeans(Dist[,2:1001])

#Generates a vector for x that is the range of averages, which can be used to plot the normal curve
x <- seq(from = min(Avgs), to = max(Avgs), by = 0.01)

#Makes a histogram of the averages of each sample, and does a density plot rather than frequency so the normal density curve can be plotted over it
ggplot() + 
  geom_histogram(bins=15, aes(Avgs, y=..density..), fill = "light gray", color = "dark gray") +  
  geom_density(aes(y=..density..)) +
  #Adds in the normal curve
  stat_function(fun=dnorm, colour = "blue", args = list(mean = 0.5, sd = sqrt((1/12)/30)), aes(x=x)) + 
  #Adds in lines to label and mean of the samples (sampling distribution mean), and the theoretical mean
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(Avgs)), size = .5, color = "black") + 
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = 0.5), size = .5, color = "blue") +
  #Adds labels for the sampling distribution mean and standard deviation, and theoretical mean and standard deviation
  geom_text(aes(x= (.65*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (1.1*dnorm(.5,.5, sqrt(1/(12*30)))), label=paste("sampling mean", signif(mean(Avgs),4), split = "") ), size = 3 ) + 
  geom_text(aes(x= (.65*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (1.05*dnorm(.5,.5, sqrt(1/(12*30)))), label=paste("theoretical mean", "0.5000", split = "") ), size = 3, color = "blue") +
  geom_text(aes(x= (.85*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (.6*dnorm(.5,.5, sqrt(1/(12*30)))), label=paste("sampling sd", signif(sd(Avgs),3), split = "") ), size = 3 ) + 
  geom_text(aes(x= (.85*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (.55*dnorm(.5,.5, sqrt(1/(12*30)))), label=paste("theoretical sd", signif(sqrt((1/12)/30),3), split = "") ), size = 3, color = "blue" )

5.

#Turns the above process into a function, where m and r are inputs and can be changed
UnifCLT <- function(m, r){
  
  U <- runif(100000)
  g1 <- ggplot() + geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.05, aes(U), fill = "black", color = "white")
  
  Dist <- data.frame(c(1:m))
  
  for(i in 1:r){
    Dist <- cbind(Dist,sample(U, m))
  }
  
  colnames(Dist) <- c("n", seq(1:r))
  Avgs <- colMeans(Dist[,2:(r+1)])
  
  x <- seq(from = min(Avgs), to = max(Avgs), by = 0.01)
  
  g2 <- ggplot() + 
    geom_histogram(bins = 15, aes(Avgs, y=..density..), fill = "light gray", color = "dark gray") +  
    geom_density(aes(y=..density..)) +
    geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(Avgs)), size = .5, color = "black") + 
    geom_vline(aes(xintercept = 0.5), size = .5, color = "blue") +
    geom_text(aes(x= (.65*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (1.1*dnorm(.5,.5, sqrt(1/(12*m)))), label=paste("sampling mean", signif(mean(Avgs),4), split = "") ), size = 3 ) + 
    geom_text(aes(x= (.65*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (1.05*dnorm(.5,.5, sqrt(1/(12*m)))), label=paste("theoretical mean", "0.5000", split = "") ), size = 3, color = "blue") +
    stat_function(fun=dnorm, colour = "blue", args = list(mean = 0.5, sd = sqrt((1/12)/m)), aes(x=x)) + 
    geom_text(aes(x= (.85*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (.6*dnorm(.5,.5, sqrt(1/(12*m)))), label=paste("sampling sd", signif(sd(Avgs),3), split = "") ), size = 3 ) + 
    geom_text(aes(x= (.85*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (.55*dnorm(.5,.5, sqrt(1/(12*m)))), label=paste("theoretical sd", signif(sqrt((1/12)/m),3), split = "") ), size = 3, color = "blue" ) 
  
  
  
    return(list(g1,g2))
}


UnifCLT(50,2000)

Part 2: Repeats the above process with a poisson distribution instead of uniform distribution

U <- rpois(100000,4)
ggplot() + geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, aes(U), fill = "black", color = "white")

Dist <- data.frame(c(1:30))
for(i in 1:1000){
  Dist <- cbind(Dist,sample(U, 30))
}

colnames(Dist) <- c("n", seq(1:1000))
Avgs <- colMeans(Dist[,2:1001])

x <- seq(from = min(Avgs), to = max(Avgs), by = 0.001)


  ggplot() + 
  geom_histogram(bins = 15, aes(Avgs, y=..density..), fill = "light gray", color = "dark gray") +  
  geom_density(aes(y=..density..)) +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(Avgs)), size = .5, color = "black") + 
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = 4), size = .5, color = "blue") +
  geom_text(aes(x= (.65*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (1.1*dnorm(4,4, sqrt(4/30))), label=paste("sampling mean", signif(mean(Avgs),4), split = "") ), size = 3 ) + 
  geom_text(aes(x= (.65*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (1.05*dnorm(4,4, sqrt(4/30))), label=paste("theoretical mean", "4.000", split = "") ), size = 3, color = "blue") +
  stat_function(fun=dnorm, colour = "blue", args = list(mean = 4, sd = sqrt(4/30)), aes(x=x)) + 
  geom_text(aes(x= (.85*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (.6*dnorm(4,4, sqrt(4/30))), label=paste("sampling sd", signif(sd(Avgs),3), split = "") ), size = 3 ) + 
  geom_text(aes(x= (.85*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (.55*dnorm(4,4, sqrt(4/30))), label=paste("theoretical sd", signif(sqrt(4/30),3), split = "") ), size = 3, color = "blue" ) 

#Turns it into a function again
PoissonCLT <- function(m, r){
  
  U <- rpois(100000,4)
  ggplot() + geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, aes(U), fill = "black", color = "white")
  
  Dist <- data.frame(c(1:m))
  
  for(i in 1:r){
    Dist <- cbind(Dist,sample(U, m))
  }
  
  colnames(Dist) <- c("n", seq(1:r))
  Avgs <- colMeans(Dist[,2:(r+1)])
  
  x <- seq(from = min(Avgs), to = max(Avgs), by = 0.01)
  
  
  ggplot() + 
    geom_histogram(bins = 15, aes(Avgs, y=..density..), fill = "light gray", color = "dark gray") +  
    geom_density(aes(y=..density..)) +
    geom_vline(aes(xintercept = mean(Avgs)), size = .5, color = "black") + 
    geom_vline(aes(xintercept = 4), size = .5, color = "blue") +
    geom_text(aes(x= (.65*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (1.1*dnorm(4,4, sqrt(4/m))), label=paste("sampling mean", signif(mean(Avgs),4), split = "") ), size = 3 ) + 
    geom_text(aes(x= (.65*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (1.05*dnorm(4,4, sqrt(4/m))), label=paste("theoretical mean", "4.000", split = "") ), size = 3, color = "blue") +
    stat_function(fun=dnorm, colour = "blue", args = list(mean = 4, sd = sqrt(4/m)), aes(x=x)) + 
    geom_text(aes(x= (.85*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (.6*dnorm(4,4, sqrt(4/m))), label=paste("sampling sd", signif(sd(Avgs),3), split = "") ), size = 3 ) + 
    geom_text(aes(x= (.85*(max(Avgs)-min(Avgs)) + min(Avgs)), y = (.55*dnorm(4,4, sqrt(4/m))), label=paste("theoretical sd", signif(sqrt(4/m),3), split = "") ), size = 3, color = "blue" ) 
  
  
  
  return(list(g1,g2))
}


UnifCLT(50,2000)
